                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13479394" author="bkempe" created="Thu, 18 Oct 2012 21:38:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;TestJob is using the new mapred interface and produces the correct output.&lt;br/&gt;
TestJobOldHadoop does not populate the row key for columns after the first.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13479398" author="bkempe" created="Thu, 18 Oct 2012 21:40:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13484579" author="bkempe" created="Thu, 25 Oct 2012 23:50:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;lastColumn also needs a duplicated ByteBuffer.&lt;br/&gt;
Otherwise, if the column name is consumed in the map/reduce code, the expression in&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/trunk/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/hadoop/ColumnFamilyRecordReader.java#L458&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/trunk/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/hadoop/ColumnFamilyRecordReader.java#L458&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
will evaluate to false and the CFRR can get into an infinite loop.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13489445" author="brandon.williams" created="Fri, 2 Nov 2012 14:32:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=bkempe&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;bkempe&quot;&gt;bkempe&lt;/a&gt; can you rebase to 1.1?  I don&apos;t see any reason to not include this there.  Looks good otherwise, thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13490696" author="bkempe" created="Mon, 5 Nov 2012 16:01:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;added patch for cassandra-1.1 branch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13491410" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 6 Nov 2012 12:25:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
